00:04:05.111 --> 00:04:08.663
 Our friend Samy tried to meet sweethearts on MySpace 

00:04:08.663 --> 00:04:10.824
 - I think it used to be before. 

00:04:10.824 --> 00:04:15.514
 He created a page on MySpace for himself. 

00:04:16.241 --> 00:04:19.075
 It made a list of all your friends, and you knew that 

00:04:19.075 --> 00:04:22.031
 if someone was cool because they had a lot of friends on MySpace. 

00:04:22.031 --> 00:04:23.852
 Samy had no friends. 

00:04:23.852 --> 00:04:27.743
 He wrote a little Javascript code that he put in his page, 

00:04:27.743 --> 00:04:29.585
 so that when you looked at his page 

00:04:29.585 --> 00:04:32.028
 you were simply added 'automagically' as a friend. 

00:04:32.028 --> 00:04:35.369
 And it skipped the entire recognition protocol 

00:04:35.369 --> 00:04:37.703
 that asked, "Is Samy really your friend?" 

00:04:37.703 --> 00:04:40.939
 But then it copied that code to your page, 

00:04:40.939 --> 00:04:43.045
 so that when someone looked at your page 

00:04:43.045 --> 00:04:45.856
 who automatically also became Samy's friend. 

00:04:45.856 --> 00:04:46.925
 (Laughter) 

00:04:46.925 --> 00:04:50.514
 And it customized your page by saying, "Samy is your hero." 

00:04:50.514 --> 00:04:52.023
 (Laughter) 

00:04:52.023 --> 00:04:56.442
