00:13:36.227 --> 00:13:39.467
 For that I need hackers. 

00:13:39.467 --> 00:13:43.508
 Because hackers have a mind out to explore, 

00:13:43.614 --> 00:13:47.407
 that is optimized to look for opportunities. 

00:13:47.407 --> 00:13:49.805
 I often illustrate this as follows. 

00:13:49.805 --> 00:13:54.676
 You have a new gadget and show it to your mother. 

00:13:55.455 --> 00:13:59.245
 Maybe she says, "What's this doing?" And you, "Mom, it's a phone." 

00:13:59.245 --> 00:14:02.566
 And she immediately knows exactly what it is for. 

00:14:02.566 --> 00:14:05.085
 But a hacker asks other questions. 

00:14:05.085 --> 00:14:08.909
 "What can I get this thing to do?" 

00:14:09.102 --> 00:14:12.029
 I take out all the screws, take the back off 

00:14:12.029 --> 00:14:13.984
 and break it into many small pieces 

00:14:13.984 --> 00:14:17.343
 and then figure out what I can make with that mess. 

00:14:17.343 --> 00:14:21.299
 That is discovery. We need that in science and technology 

00:14:21.299 --> 00:14:23.439
 to find the possibilities. 

00:14:23.439 --> 00:14:26.818
 In the lab I try to apply that way of thinking 

00:14:26.818 --> 00:14:29.843
 on some of the biggest problems people have. 

00:14:29.843 --> 00:14:34.152
 We are working on malaria at the request of Bill Gates. 

00:14:34.152 --> 00:14:36.863
 That is how we tried to solve malaria. 

00:14:36.863 --> 00:14:39.070
 This is a real 1940s ad. 

00:14:39.070 --> 00:14:43.205
 We eradicated malaria in the US by spraying DDT everywhere. 

00:14:44.455 --> 00:14:48.505
 In the lab, we work hard to understand the problem. 

00:14:48.505 --> 00:14:53.658
 This is a high-speed video, we have a boulder from a video camera 

00:14:53.658 --> 00:14:56.293
 to learn how mosquitoes fly. 

00:14:56.293 --> 00:14:58.931
 You can see that they swim in the air earlier. 

00:14:58.931 --> 00:15:01.299
 We actually have no idea how they fly. 

00:15:01.299 --> 00:15:03.740
 But we have a nice video camera, so we - 

00:15:03.740 --> 00:15:05.534
 (Laughter) 

00:15:05.534 --> 00:15:08.535
 Yes, it costs more than a Ferrari. 

00:15:08.535 --> 00:15:12.395
 In any case, we found a number of ways to get rid of mosquitoes. 

00:15:12.395 --> 00:15:14.807
 We fire them with laser beams. 

00:15:14.807 --> 00:15:19.318
 You get this if you have all kinds of scientists 

00:15:19.318 --> 00:15:21.318
 and put a laser nerd together in a room. 

00:15:21.318 --> 00:15:25.237
 At first people thought it was funny, 

00:15:25.237 --> 00:15:30.076
 but we found out we could build this with regular electronics. 

00:15:30.076 --> 00:15:33.390
 With the CCD of a webcam, 

00:15:33.390 --> 00:15:36.590
 the laser of a Blu-ray burner, 

00:15:36.590 --> 00:15:40.212
 the laser galvo comes from a laser printer. 

00:15:40.212 --> 00:15:43.220
 We do motion detection on a GPU processor 

00:15:43.220 --> 00:15:45.414
 as you find it in a video game system. 

00:15:45.414 --> 00:15:47.613
 All things that follow Moore's law. 

00:15:47.613 --> 00:15:50.228
 So it is not going to be too expensive. 

00:15:50.228 --> 00:15:52.466
 We want these laser systems 

00:15:52.466 --> 00:15:56.317
 around a building or village 

00:15:56.317 --> 00:15:59.507
 and just shoot all the mosquitoes that come at the people. 

00:15:59.507 --> 00:16:02.800
 And we would like to do that for your backyard. 

00:16:02.800 --> 00:16:04.763
 We could also start protecting crops. 

00:16:04.763 --> 00:16:06.489
 Our team is now investigating 

00:16:06.489 --> 00:16:09.725
 what they need to do the same 

00:16:09.725 --> 00:16:12.899
 for the plague that is about two-thirds 

00:16:12.899 --> 00:16:16.477
 of the orange plantations in Florida. 

00:16:18.102 --> 00:16:20.719
 People first laughed at it. 

00:16:20.719 --> 00:16:23.441
 This is a video of our system at work. 

00:16:23.441 --> 00:16:26.119
 We follow the mosquitoes as they fly around. 

00:16:26.119 --> 00:16:28.622
 Those visors come from our computer. 

00:16:28.622 --> 00:16:30.713
 It looks at them, sees them move 

00:16:30.713 --> 00:16:34.217
 and then point a laser at it to measure their wing beat frequency. 

00:16:34.217 --> 00:16:37.424
 That reveals which mosquito it is. 

00:16:37.424 --> 00:16:40.325
 An Anopheles stephensi? A female? 

00:16:40.325 --> 00:16:44.912
 And if so, she'll get a deadly laser shot. 

00:16:44.912 --> 00:16:46.981
 (Laughter) 

00:16:46.981 --> 00:16:48.753
 This works in a lab. 

00:16:48.753 --> 00:16:51.879
 Now we are going to test it in the field. 

00:16:51.879 --> 00:16:54.735
 All this is done in the Intellectual Ventures Lab 

00:16:54.735 --> 00:16:56.425
 in Seattle where I work. 

00:16:56.425 --> 00:16:59.356
 We try some of the most difficult problems 

00:16:59.356 --> 00:17:01.626
 that people have to deal with. 

00:17:01.626 --> 00:17:03.468
 This is the crucial shot. 

00:17:03.468 --> 00:17:07.171
 We just burn off his wing with a UV laser. 

00:17:07.171 --> 00:17:08.848
 He's not coming back. 

00:17:08.848 --> 00:17:12.071
 (Applause) 

00:17:12.071 --> 00:17:15.874
 His wing just evaporated. 

00:17:15.874 --> 00:17:18.636
 They love it. I mean, you know. 

00:17:18.636 --> 00:17:20.769
 Never received a call from PETA or anyone else. 

00:17:20.769 --> 00:17:23.226
 I mean it's the perfect enemy. 

00:17:23.226 --> 00:17:26.378
 There is simply no one who comes to the rescue of mosquitoes. 

00:17:26.378 --> 00:17:29.660
 Sometimes we exaggerate. 

00:17:29.660 --> 00:17:32.093
 Anyway, I'm leaving now. 

00:17:32.093 --> 00:17:35.141
 This is the Intellectual Ventures Lab where I work. 

00:17:35.141 --> 00:17:38.565
 In principle, we use any kind of scientist 

00:17:38.565 --> 00:17:42.185
 and every tool in the world to develop crazy inventions. 

00:17:42.185 --> 00:17:43.537
 Thanks. 

00:17:43.537 --> 00:17:47.265
 (Applause) 

